<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 31 at 7:51AM EST  by NWS Wilmington</headline>
<description>...Patchy Dense Fog this Morning...
Patches of locally dense fog, with visibilities reduced to one-
quarter mile, will be possible across inland portions of northeast
South Carolina and southeast North Carolina this morning. Impacts
include hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you. Due to the patchy nature of the dense fog,
motorists should be prepared for rapidly changing visibility
conditions until all of the fog burns off later this morning.</description>
